üõ†Ô∏è COMMON MISTAKES TO ADDRESS (High Engagement Content)
Beginner Mistakes (from Pro Manicurists):

Skipping base coat (causes staining + poor adhesion)
Applying thick coats (only dries on top, smudges easily)
Not dehydrating/cleaning nails first (oils prevent bonding)
Filing wet nails (weakens and breaks them)
Cutting cuticles aggressively (causes infection risk)
Not sealing the free edge with top coat (chips fast)
Using old/expired products (harbor bacteria)
Pressing too hard while painting (damages nail bed)
Shaking polish bottle (creates bubbles)
Painting on dirty/oily nails (vinegar prep essential)
Not letting layers dry between coats
Using fans/blow dryers to speed drying (causes bubbles)
Soaking nails in water before painting (causes puffing/chipping)
Forgetting cuticle oil aftercare (manicure lifts/peels)


